Yes, you can have constant fields in interfaces, but you are right when you say that &quot;it seems contrary to what an interface is supposed to do&quot;, as it is not a good practice. Why would you want to have all your classes that implement an interface with the same constants? You could simply have them in the class that uses them, or if you really need to export them somehow, have them in a separate class utiliy like this:

    public class Constants {
